WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.634 --> 00:00:04.050
FEMALE SPEAKER:
For over 20 years,

00:00:04.050 --> 00:00:06.810
Duggan McDonnell has been making
his mark on the West Coast

00:00:06.810 --> 00:00:10.020
beverage scene, distinguishing
himself at such San Francisco

00:00:10.020 --> 00:00:12.720
gems as the Redwood
Room and Absinthe.

00:00:12.720 --> 00:00:15.010
He is the founder
and owner of Cantina

00:00:15.010 --> 00:00:17.480
and has designed cocktails
for the Sundance Film

00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:20.190
Festival, Aspen Food
and Wine, the Omni

00:00:20.190 --> 00:00:21.700
Hotel, and many others.

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:23.800
He is also a winemaker
and distiller

00:00:23.800 --> 00:00:27.030
and lectures at the Culinary
Institute of America.

00:00:27.030 --> 00:00:29.520
Passionate about writing,
as well as mixology,

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:31.160
he has authored
articles and recently

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:32.930
published his first book.

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:34.780
"Drinking the Devil's
Acre-- a Love Letter

00:00:34.780 --> 00:00:37.010
from San Francisco
and Her Cocktails"

00:00:37.010 --> 00:00:39.610
is at once a bold primer
on modern mixology,

00:00:39.610 --> 00:00:42.660
a barman's memoir, and a
dive into San Francisco's

00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:44.580
rich cocktail history.

00:00:44.580 --> 00:00:47.096
Please join me in
welcoming Duggan McDonnell.

00:00:47.096 --> 00:00:49.376
[APPLAUSE]

